<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="638" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,646,595,646]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">ETYMOLOGY. — Species named after the distinctive colouration of its pronotum.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="638" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,648,669,746]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
DIAGNOSIS. — Species close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[435,541,669,693]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[435,541,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[550,643,669,693]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from which it can be readily separated by the uniform black colouration of its pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="638" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[112,648,787,1288]" box="[113,394,787,813]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
DESCRIPTION (
<typeStatus box="[275,386,792,811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[112,648,787,1288]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
Species very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[354,466,818,844]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[354,466,818,844]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[472,568,818,845]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Global colouration quite homogeneously ochre, except for black pronotum. Characters as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[530,647,881,907]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[530,647,881,907]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[113,214,913,940]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except for: TII with 4 apical spurs, the inner spurs longer than the outer.TIII serrulation: inner spine number: 0 between apex and spur 1, and between spurs 1 and 2; 1 or 2 between spurs 2 and 3; 2 between spurs 3 and 4; 7 or 8 above subapical spur 4; number of outer spines: 0 between apex and spur 1; 3 between spurs 1 and 2; 5 between spurs 2 and 3; 4 or 5 between spurs 3 and 4, 14 above subapical spur 4. Basitarsi III as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[173,288,1198,1224]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[173,288,1198,1224]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[296,396,1198,1225]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but with 3 or 4 dorsal spines in addition to apical one. HWs and FWs as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[142,256,1261,1287]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[142,256,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[263,360,1261,1288]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[111,648,1325,1573]" box="[113,237,1325,1351]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis box="[113,237,1325,1351]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Colouration</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[111,648,1325,1573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Head almost entirely ochre, the head dorsum, upper part of the face, tibiae and femora apex somewhat darker; eye dorsal third lighter. Pronotum black, with ochre margins; a wider ochre band along the posterior margin of dorsal disc and a narrow one along the lower margin of lateral lobe. Legs without distinct coloured stripes or rings.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,647,1610,1700]" box="[113,166,1610,1636]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis box="[113,166,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,647,1610,1700]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
FWs and stridulatory apparatus similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[113,227,1673,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi">
<emphasis box="[113,227,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; file with 38 stridulatory teeth (n = 1);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[677,1197,317,373]" box="[786,1197,317,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[786,1197,317,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Lpron lpron LFW lFW LFIII LTIII File</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[677,1197,317,373]" box="[677,1191,354,373]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<typeStatus box="[677,763,354,373]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Holotype</typeStatus>
2.9 4.9 14.7 7.2 11 10 32
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[674,1210,438,591]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
harp with 9 veins, 5 of which crossed by CuP; mirror crossed by 2 veins, the upper one beginning below (= more distally) the junction between the mirror and c1 cell; lateral field: R bifurcated 19 times. Subgenital plate as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[915,1028,564,590]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[915,1028,564,590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1035,1132,564,591]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[675,1209,627,718]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[677,836,627,654]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1024,1134,628,654]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi">
<emphasis box="[1024,1134,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in size and structure, in particular for the pseudepiphallic sclerite and lophi, the parameres as on 
<figureCitation box="[1093,1202,691,718]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="15.[113,124,1349,1366]" captionTargetBox="[119,1207,231,1305]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[111,1211,213,1307]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIG. 5. — A-D, Phaloria chopardi (Willemse, 1925) n. comb.; A-C, male genitalia, ♂ MNHN-ENSIF2102, in dorsal (A), ventral (B) and lateral (C) views; D, right pseudepiphallic paramere, ventral view; E, P. nigricollis n. sp., male genitalia, ♂ MNHN-ENSIF2113, right pseudepiphallic paramere, ventral view; F, G, P. nigricollis n. sp. (?), female copulatory papilla in lateral (F) and dorsal (G) views, ♀ MNHN-ENSIF2114. Scale bars: A-C, F, G, 1 mm; D, E, 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: see text." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398353/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Figure 5E</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[677,822,755,813]" box="[677,822,755,780]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
<emphasis box="[677,822,755,780]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Measurements</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[677,822,755,813]" box="[677,804,786,813]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
See 
<tableCitation box="[718,804,786,813]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="19.[677,688,220,237]" captionText="TABLE 6. — Measurements (in mm) of Phaloria nigricollis n. sp. holotype. Abbreviations: see text." pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Table 6.</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="638" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[674,1212,850,1352]" box="[677,767,850,876]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[674,1212,850,1352]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">
Two females from 
<collectingCountry box="[885,980,881,908]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[993,1158,881,908]" country="Vanuatu" name="Shefa" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Shefa province</collectingRegion>
, Epi island (Mt. Alempe, 1935-1936, E. Aubert de la Rüe [MNHN-ENSIF2114, 2115]), could also belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="Desutter-Grandcolas, 2009" authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" box="[674,797,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[674,797,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P. nigricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[803,863,976,1003]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, with which they share the same pattern of pronotum colouration. In 
<specimenCount box="[1089,1208,1008,1035]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
distinct yellowish spots are however visible on the face and cheeks. Th ese females have an ovipositor which is much smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desutter-Grandcolas" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Willemse" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[966,1075,1103,1129]" class="Insecta" family="Phalangopsidae" genus="Phaloria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chopardi" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[966,1075,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">P.chopardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1079,1170,1103,1130]" pageId="19" pageNumber="638" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see measurements); their subgenital plate is large, with a deeply concave posterior margin; their FW venation shows 3 anal veins, A1 bifurcated with or without distal anastomosis, CuP and CuA bifurcated twice or 3 times each. Their copulatory papilla is hardly sclerotized only dorsally, its apex sinuated dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[684,796,1325,1352]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="15.[113,124,1349,1366]" captionTargetBox="[119,1207,231,1305]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[111,1211,213,1307]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIG. 5. — A-D, Phaloria chopardi (Willemse, 1925) n. comb.; A-C, male genitalia, ♂ MNHN-ENSIF2102, in dorsal (A), ventral (B) and lateral (C) views; D, right pseudepiphallic paramere, ventral view; E, P. nigricollis n. sp., male genitalia, ♂ MNHN-ENSIF2113, right pseudepiphallic paramere, ventral view; F, G, P. nigricollis n. sp. (?), female copulatory papilla in lateral (F) and dorsal (G) views, ♀ MNHN-ENSIF2114. Scale bars: A-C, F, G, 1 mm; D, E, 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: see text." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5398353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5398353/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Fig. 5F, G</figureCitation>
). See 
<tableCitation box="[857,936,1325,1352]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="20.[127,138,220,237]" captionText="TABLE 7. — Measurements (in mm) of two females of Phaloria nigricollis n. sp. originating from Epi island. Abbreviations: see text." pageId="19" pageNumber="638">Table 7</tableCitation>
for measurements.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
